column5: What an insane fishing trip. I don't even know how many of the World's Greatest Sportfish we landed yesterday, but it was just amazing. The rod pumping, the explosive strikes and the thrill of landing Ontario's most esteemed species just kept us on our toes. And the frying pan/our stomachs thanked us. What a day with Mr. Rock Bass.          Okay, I promise, first and last rock bass report of the year from me.
LOL!!!!  My oldman and I were trying to jig up some pickerel yesterday, but we only managed to tie into 1 small OOS smallie and some giant pumpkinseeds!
when no other fish are biteing rock bass never pass a free meal lol
